<%#
  This is the shared plain-text layout for all mailer views. <%= yield %> renders
  the specific email body from each mailer action's .text.erb template.

  To activate this layout, an agent needs to:
  1. Add any shared plain-text header/footer around <%= yield %> (e.g., app name,
     unsubscribe instructions).
  2. Ensure each mailer action has a matching .text.erb template alongside its
     .html.erb template so Rails sends a proper multipart (HTML + text) email.
  3. See app/mailers/application_mailer.rb for full SMTP setup instructions.
%>
<%= yield %>
